×031Collidating with a Planet×
×031=========================×
So  there was a lot of advert spam at this party. And
just  as  usual  people deliver flyers and sheets for
everything  between  a new irc-channel and a new demo
party   taking   place.

Some  guys in red t-shirts (Breakpoint orgaz were red
marsians  aswell!)  handled  over  advertisment   for
french  party  'Saturne'.  I took the freedom to grab
them  for  a  little  chat. This is the output of it:

Last was made in 1997, and then it was like 30% Amiga
and  70%  PC.  The  reason  for  this  reunion of old
party-staff  was  that  the  era until 1997 they were
studying  and in school, now in the year of 2005 they
are  all  older, having their jobs, and time for this
again. The most people come from France, but previous
years,  they also had visitors from Spain, Italy, and
Germany.

I  also took the chance to ask what the Saturne orgaz
expected from Amiga releases during the October days:  
   ×008"Well, less 3d and more design would be nice"×
The info sheet for Saturne Party 2005 reveals support
for other platforms such as c64 platform, Atari, CPC,
PSX  etc.  so  it seems like a try for multiplatform.
Earlier  years,  the biggest attraction (and a reason
for  attending) as an Amiga scener was because of the
French  group  ×031Bomb×,  and  their  golden years around
middle  of  the  90's.  For reasons beeing there this
year,  you  better  check their homepage. I wish them
Good Luck!

